Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glucosuria, bilirubinuria, and abnormal urine appearance, suggesting impaired renal function, likely chronic kidney disease with possible nephrotic features. Elevated chloride and low COâ‚‚ may indicate metabolic acidosis. Blood glucose and HbA1c are within normal limits, making diabetes less likely. Recommend urgent nephrology evaluation and further workup for renal pathology.
